import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['price'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of price over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    avg_price = data['price'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.axhline(y=avg_price, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Price: {avg_price:.2f}')
    ax.bar('Average Price', avg_price, color='b')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average price?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['price'] = pd.to_numeric(data['price'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['price'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['price'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of price?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['price'] = pd.to_numeric(data['price'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['price'])
    ax.set_title('What is the highest and lowest price?')
    ax.axhline(y=data['price'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {data["price"].max():.2f}')
    ax.axhline(y=data['price'].min(), color='g', linestyle='--', label=f'Min: {data["price"].min():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
